subSubSection.paragraph:
Ghatsa
is distinguished from
Homalopteroides
by having small and smooth scales (data only available for
G . montana
) vs. large and wart-like/keeled scales; ca. 53 (data only available for
G . montana
) vs. 14–25 predorsal scales; 59 –ca. 101 vs. 33–52 lateral-line scales; truncated or slightly emarginated vs. forked caudal fin; and adipose keel present (data only available for
G . montana
) vs. absent.
